                       <div id="pressRelease">
    <h3>Call for Entries Open for 2014 CES Innovations Design and Engineering Awards Honoring Best in CE Innovation</h3>
    <h4>CEA Accepting Submissions Through September 13</h4>
    <em>Arlington,&nbsp;VA&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;08/12/2013</em>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)<sup> &reg;</sup> today announced that entries for the 2014 CES Innovations Design and Engineering Awards will be accepted now through Sept. 13, 2013. The 2014 <a href="http://cesweb.org/Awards/CES-Innovations-Awards.aspx">Best of Innovations Honorees</a> will be announced Nov. 12, 2013, at the <a href="http://cesweb.org/Events/CES-Unveiled/CES-Unveiled-NEW-YORK.aspx">CES Unveiled NEW YORK</a> press conference and showcased at the 2014 International CES<sup>&reg;</sup>. Owned and produced by CEA, the 2014 CES is the world&rsquo;s leading innovation event, and is scheduled for Jan. 7-10, 2014, in Las Vegas, Nevada.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
The annual competition honors outstanding design and engineering across <a href="http://cesweb.org/Awards/CES-Innovations-Awards/Award-Categories.aspx">29 consumer electronics categories</a>. Three new product categories have been added to the 2014 awards program:<br />
&nbsp;
<ol>
	<li>
		<strong>3D Printing &amp; Additive Manufacturing:</strong> This category includes 3D printers, accessories, software, platforms, and any electronic device that facilitates the use of additive manufacturing.</li>
	<li>
		<strong>In-Vehicle Experience:</strong> Entries include entire motor vehicles in which the cabin experience is enhanced through the innovative use of electronic components.</li>
	<li>
		<strong>Wearable Technologies:</strong> This category will feature electronic devices typically worn by consumers that use sensors for navigation, information-gathering, communicating information, or other sensory enhancements.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;<br />
&ldquo;The Innovations awards program continues to grow in recognition and popularity as a unique opportunity for tech innovators to gain exposure among the consumer electronics industry,&rdquo; said Karen Chupka, senior vice president, International CES and corporate business strategy, CEA. &ldquo;The addition of these three new categories allows us to highlight design and engineering advances in exciting, emerging new product categories. We look forward to seeing a glimpse into the tech future with this year&rsquo;s entries.&rdquo;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Media and analysts will have an opportunity to see this year&rsquo;s Best of Innovations Honorees in person during <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Events/CES-Unveiled/CES-Unveiled-LAS-VEGAS.aspx">CES Unveiled LAS VEGAS: The Official Media Event of CES</a>, featuring dozens of tabletop product demonstrations and industry networking. CES Unveiled LAS VEGAS is scheduled for 4-7 p.m. Sunday, January 5, at Mandalay Bay in Las Vegas. Credentialed media and analysts are invited to attend this exclusive event.<br />
<br />
The 2014 Innovations Awards program is open to all companies, regardless of CES exhibitor status. Products entered must debut for sale in U.S. retail outlets or on the Internet between April 1, 2013, and April 1, 2014. <a href="http://cesweb.org/Awards/CES-Innovations-Awards/How-to-Enter.aspx">Submit your product</a> here.<br />
<br />
The 2014 CES will feature more than 3,200 exhibitors unveiling the latest consumer technology products and services across 15 product categories. For more information on the 2014 International CES, visit <a href="http://www.cesweb.org">CESweb.org.</a><br />
<br />
<strong>Note to Editors: The official name of the global technology event is &ldquo;International CES.&rdquo; Subsequent references to the show can be shortened to &ldquo;CES.&rdquo; Please do not use &ldquo;Consumer Electronics Show&rdquo; to refer to the International CES.</strong><br />
<br />
&nbsp;
    </div>
    <div class="pressAboutCEA">
        <strong>About CES</strong>
        <p>The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade association promoting growth in the $203 billion U.S. consumer electronics industry. More than 2,000 companies enjoy the benefits of CEA membership, including legislative advocacy, market research, technical training and education, industry promotion, standards development and the fostering of business and strategic relationships.&nbsp;CEA also owns and produces the International CES &ndash; The Global Stage for Innovation. All profits from CES are reinvested into CEA&rsquo;s industry services.&nbsp; Follow CES online at <a href="http://www.CESweb.org">www.CESweb.org</a> and through social media. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
    </div>
    <div class="pressContact">
        <strong>Press Contacts:</strong>
